other_tests.findings: The appendix is dilated to 8 mm and filled with fluid; there is failure of contrast opacification. Moderate circumferential wall thickening and hyperenhancement are present. There is mild surrounding fat stranding and simple free fluid in the right lower quadrant. Scattered sub-3-mm ground-glass nodules are noted at the lung bases. No pleural effusions. The heart is normal in size, without pericardial effusion. Liver enhances homogeneously, gallbladder is partially collapsed, pancreas normal. Kidneys excrete contrast promptly and symmetrically. Moderate amount of retained fecal material throughout the colon and rectum.
